text:
$40 for steamed pork momo, gobi manchurian, and chicken lollipop.

Should whatsapp the lady for order first and then wait around 30 minutes.

Momo: skin is thick, but ok la

Gobi manchurian: my fav

Chicken lollipop: seem a bit raw/pink inside

Came across this store on GrabFood and gave it a try. I found the Momos wonderful! Great taste and delivered piping hot! I am fine with the price as the quality of food is fantastic! Will definitely order again!

Review date: 08 June 2024
Ordered chicken and pork momo, along with Gobi Manchurian and chicken chowmein yesterday. For some reason, the Momo was sour and it had a masala flavour, something very different from what I had tasted in India among the Tibetan community. A bit disappointing though with the Momo.

Chicken chowmein and Gobi Manchurian was good and the quantity of chicken chowmein was quite large.

I ordered Chicken Lollipop, which was clearly mentioned as having 6 pieces, but upon delivery, I only received  order with 4 pieces.
I attempted to contact the restaurant via phone to address the issue, but no one responded to my calls

Best momos I ever had in Singapore after awhile.Chatpate Momos were spicy and tangy.Placed my order through Oddle conveniently.They are also available on Grab and Foodpanda.Wide variety of menu.Plan to try more soon!..Yums ❤️
